profile.occupation: CFO / General Manager at Loud and Clear, Inc.
profile.headline: CFO / General Manager
profile.summary:
Operations Manager with strong skills in accounting, finance, and sales with a background in professional services, membership, manufacturing, and food industries. Experience encompasses managing Fortune 500 franchise, conducting manufacturing financial audits to identify improvement opportunities, and developing and executing strategies to improve revenue streams. 

Successes include: led the team to achieve store customer service score 11% higher than corporate average; reduced annual expenses by $48,000; and increased sales by 8%. 

Management:
•	Oversight of average annual revenue - $3 to 3.5M – 70-75 employees including management staff of 8 with an average employee retention rate of 2 – 5 years.
•	Managed franchise and delivered increased sales year-over-year
•	Achieved store customer satisfaction score of 66% when the corporate average was 55%
•	Led store to a Corporate Score Card ranking of 13 out of 36 stores
•	Selected to represent McDonald’s at the worldwide convention - 2016

Accounting/Finance:
•	Reduced reporting effort by 16-man hours/month
•	Eliminated need to use the line of credit and saved $48,000 annually in expenses
•	Collected $600,000 in aged receivables within six months
•	Improved receivables inflow from 9 months to 2 months
•	Resolved invoicing/consignment issues saving $550,000
•	Participated on the team conducting 25 audits within one year within budget
•	Grew stock portfolio during the recession and outperformed market

Sales/Marketing:
•	Increased membership sales by 8% 
•	Increased membership from 500 to 650 in the first year
•	Maintained 75% of membership throughout the engagement 
•	Managed 125 clients – achieving billable hours and gross margins
•	Built business relationships resulting in customer loyalty

SKILLS
•	Accounting/Auditing
•	Relationship Building
•	Motivational Leadership Practices
•	Operations
•	Profit & Loss Principles
•	Sales Strategy
•	Systems and Procedures

experiences.title: General Manager
experiences.description:
My family was one of the original McDonald’s franchisees in South Central Michigan and Northeast Indiana.  Later returned to work for McDonald's Corporation as a general manager.  I was responsible for building the profitability of the restaurants by growing sales and guest counts while controlling food and labor costs.

•	Built both sales and guest counts through properly managing our systems and procedures to promote Quality, Service, and Cleanliness.  
•	Fostered a pleasant work environment for our crew members.
•	Monitored store operations for proper quality, procedures, and cost efficiencies.
•	Implemented control routines and coach crew on procedures wherever necessary.  
•	Recruited new employees and manage training program for entire crew.
•	Identified and developed potential candidates for management promotions.
•	Managed daily labor costs and advised other managers to do the same throughout the month.
